Reasoning: The paper deals with generating contour drawings from images, which is a problem in both computer graphics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a learning-based method, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves collecting a new dataset, which is related to cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper mentions fine-tuning on BSDS500, which is a benchmark dataset for salient object detection, falling under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
